# Wisp Docker + Cloudflare Tunnel deployment — copy to .env.deploy and fill in.
# Used both by compose interpolation (TUNNEL_TOKEN, build arg) and as the app
# container's runtime environment (env_file):
#
#   docker compose --env-file .env.deploy up -d --build

# ── Cloudflare Tunnel ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Zero Trust → Networks → Tunnels → Create a tunnel (Cloudflared) → copy the
# token. Then add a Public Hostname on the tunnel pointing at Service
# http://app:3007 (the compose-internal address of the wisp container).
TUNNEL_TOKEN=eyJ...

# ── Supabase (Settings → API Keys; new key format only) ─────────────────────
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=sb_secret_...

# ── Behind Cloudflare, exactly one trusted proxy hop appends the client IP to
# X-Forwarded-For, so the default depth of 1 is correct — set explicitly here
# so a compose change can't silently break rate limiting / audit hashing.
WISP_TRUSTED_PROXY_DEPTH=1

# Recommended: stable salt so audit IP hashes correlate across restarts.
WISP_IP_SALT=some-long-random-string

# Optional: enables POST /api/sweep (expiry cleanup — point pg_cron at
# https://<your-tunnel-hostname>/api/sweep with this bearer secret).
# WISP_SWEEP_SECRET=some-long-random-string

# ── Email (Resend) — omit to log emails to the container console instead ────
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# WISP_EMAIL_FROM=Wisp <wisp@your-verified-domain.com>

# ── Clerk sender accounts (optional; use LIVE keys in production) ────────────
# The publishable key is baked into the browser bundle at IMAGE BUILD time —
# changing it requires `docker compose --env-file .env.deploy up -d --build`.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_...
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
